---
description: Prevents irreversible side effects before explicit confirmation in plan/review/approval flows.
alwaysApply: false
---

# Plan confirmation gate

## Rule

When a workflow asks the user to confirm a plan, quote, destructive operation,
charge, send, deploy, publish, or external action, no irreversible side effect may
occur before confirmation.

## Requirements

1. Persist a pending state that cannot be confused with active/running/sent.
2. Store enough plan details to resume safely after refresh.
3. Confirmation must validate the pending item still belongs to the user and is
   still confirmable.
4. Cancellation must clean up holds, temp files, locks, and optimistic state.
5. Duplicate confirmations must be idempotent.
6. Workers and socket listeners must treat pending as parked, not in flight.
7. UI should make clear what will happen on confirm.

## Pre-commit check

- [ ] No external action before confirm.
- [ ] Pending state survives refresh.
- [ ] Confirm/cancel are idempotent.
- [ ] Workers do not process parked plans.
